abstract: Mr. Yang’s haul over the last three months is almost double what he raised over the rest of his presidential campaign.
snippet: Mr. Yang’s haul over the last three months is almost double what he raised over the rest of his presidential campaign.
lead_paragraph: The entrepreneur Andrew Yang announced Wednesday that his presidential campaign had raised $10 million in the third quarter of 2019, a significant sum for the political outsider who was almost entirely unknown when he began his long-shot bid for the Democratic nomination 20 months ago.

abstract: A forum organized by Giffords and March for Our Lives, two years after a mass shooting in Las Vegas, aimed to bring gun policy to the forefront of the Democratic primary.
snippet: A forum organized by Giffords and March for Our Lives, two years after a mass shooting in Las Vegas, aimed to bring gun policy to the forefront of the Democratic primary.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — The 2020 Democratic presidential candidates on Wednesday expressed their collective support for sweeping new gun control measures, appearing at a forum in a city still grieving after a gunman massacred 58 concertgoers two years and one day ago.

headline_main: DealBook Briefing: It’s Elizabeth Warren vs. Mark Zuckerberg

abstract: In the last three months, Bernie Sanders raised $25.3 million. Pete Buttigieg raised $19.1 million and Kamala Harris $11.6 million, at a time when donations signal viability.
snippet: In the last three months, Bernie Sanders raised $25.3 million. Pete Buttigieg raised $19.1 million and Kamala Harris $11.6 million, at a time when donations signal viability.
lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders has produced the biggest fund-raising quarter of the Democratic primary, as his campaign announced on Tuesday that he had taken in $25.3 million over the last three months. Now the big questions looming over the donor race are whether Senator Elizabeth Warren will surpass him, and whether former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. will trail far behind.

abstract: The huge infusion of money confirms that President Trump is building an enormous war chest heading into the 2020 election.
snippet: The huge infusion of money confirms that President Trump is building an enormous war chest heading into the 2020 election.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s re-election campaign and the Republican National Committee raised a combined $125 million in the last three months, Republican Party officials said on Tuesday, setting a presidential fund-raising record.

headline_main: Trump Campaign and R.N.C. Raise $125 Million in Third Fund-Raising Quarter

abstract: The California senator raised about half of her total funds from digital fund-raising, a campaign spokesman said.
snippet: The California senator raised about half of her total funds from digital fund-raising, a campaign spokesman said.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris of California has raised $11.6 million in the past three months, her campaign said on Tuesday, a total that almost identically matches her fund-raising totals from previous quarters, when she also raised around $12 million.

headline_main: Which 2020 Democrats Raised the Most Money This Summer?

abstract: Mr. Booker raised $6 million in the past three months, and he met a $1.7 million goal over 10 days that he said was needed to keep his campaign alive.
snippet: Mr. Booker raised $6 million in the past three months, and he met a $1.7 million goal over 10 days that he said was needed to keep his campaign alive.
lead_paragraph: Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey raised more than $6 million in the past three months, his campaign said on Tuesday, his best fund-raising quarter yet but one that still falls short of the leading candidates’ hauls.
